Module cathedral.game
Package de.fhkiel.ki.cathedral.game

Enum Class Building

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Enum<Building>
de.fhkiel.ki.cathedral.game.Building
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Comparable<Building>, Constable
public enum Building extends Enum<Building>
The enum Building defines all possible builings in the game. These buildings are final and can not be changed on runtime.

Buildings have an id, a name, a Color, the number of them in a normal game, their score value and how it is Turnable
Their form is described with a list of Position and each possible Direction has an own form. These can be accessed through turn(Direction)
Derived from the form are the corners of a building which are all positions directly touching positions of the form in a Direction. The form positions are not contained in these lists. These can be accessed through corners(Direction)
Derived from the form is the silhouette of a building which are all positions directly surrounding positions of the form. The form positions are not contained in these lists. These can be accessed through silhouette(Direction)


The forms of the individual building are shown in the following format in this documentation:
        0째   |    90째   |    180째  |    270째
    -1  0  1 | -1  0  1 | -1  0  1 | -1  0  1 x
 -1          |          |          |
  0     X    |     X    |     X    |     X
  1          |          |          |
  y
X shows the center of the form. O is a part of the form.
Depending on the Turnable type, only certain forms are shown.
Since:
1.0
